{"author":{"id":"d090680751e9d81548e628ee372337dbb14df0993593a8afe125eaa85e30d5d8"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1688009278,"nonce":"k/T400swz4d5ju0Fshaz6B042Z0=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5qGZ1e","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5377","origin":"github"},"title":"DADA2 creates faulty output with `fastqsanger` input","message":"A user reported an issue with `dada2_filterAndTrim` - this is another case where the tool infers output datatype based on the input and this now seems to fail (could it be a 23.0 bug?).\n\n- Input: `fastqsanger`\n- Output: `fastqsanger` datatype assigned to `fastqsanger.gz`\n\nI created an additional test to catch the above issue:\n\n```xml\n\u003c!-- paired data in paired collection with uncompressed input --\u003e\n\u003ctest expect_num_outputs=\"4\"\u003e\n    \u003cconditional name=\"paired_cond\"\u003e\n        \u003cparam name=\"paired_select\" value=\"paired\"/\u003e\n        \u003cparam name=\"reads\"\u003e\n            \u003ccollection type=\"paired\"\u003e\n                \u003celement name=\"forward\" value=\"F3D0_S188_L001_R1_001.fastq\" ftype=\"fastqsanger\"/\u003e\n                \u003celement name=\"reverse\" value=\"F3D0_S188_L001_R2_001.fastq\" ftype=\"fastqsanger\"/\u003e\n            \u003c/collection\u003e\n        \u003c/param\u003e\n    \u003c/conditional\u003e\n    \u003coutput_collection name=\"paired_output\" type=\"paired\" count=\"2\"\u003e\n        \u003celement name=\"forward\" value=\"filterAndTrim_F3D0_R1.fq\" ftype=\"fastqsanger\" /\u003e\n        \u003celement name=\"reverse\" value=\"filterAndTrim_F3D0_R2.fq\" ftype=\"fastqsanger\" /\u003e\n    \u003c/output_collection\u003e\n    \u003coutput name=\"outtab\" value=\"F3D0_S188_L001_R1_001.tab\" ftype=\"tabular\" lines_diff=\"2\"\u003e\n        \u003cassert_contents\u003e\n            \u003chas_text text=\"745\" /\u003e\n            \u003chas_text text=\"750\" /\u003e\n        \u003c/assert_contents\u003e\n    \u003c/output\u003e\n\u003c/test\u003e\n```","files":null}]}